Male genitalia:
Pygophore trapezoidal. Dorsal rim uniformly concave in dorsal view (
Fig. 18
) median projection of dorsal rim long, sinuosity shallow; superior process of dorsal rim tooth-like. Ventral rim slightly sinuous, convex medially in ventral view (
Fig. 20
). In posterior view, ventral rim protuberant medially; superior layer of ventral rim excavated in V-shape in posterior view (
Fig. 19
). Paramere: margin connecting basal and apical process slightly concave; apical process somewhat spatulate at apex; middle process not developed (
Fig. 26
).
